[SN]TITLE[SN]
Gang of Four: Could the Labour Party split again?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
It's the 35th anniversary this month of the Limehouse Declaration that led to the founding of the Social Democratic Party (SDP).

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
21 January 2016 Last updated at 11:45 GMT
Back in 1981, the so-called "Gang of Four" senior Labour politicians broke off - partly in protest at the leftward drift of their party.
Could history repeat itself? Very possibly, according to two surviving members of the Gang of Four - Shirley Williams and David Owen. They spoke to BBC Newsnight's Lewis Goodall as part of a look back at that landmark moment.
